(20, 118, 'Welcome to Diocese of Dar Es Salaam', 'welcome-to-diocese-of-dar-es-salaam', '<p style="color: #000000; text-align: justify;">Diocese of Dar es Salaam was established in 1963. It occupies an area of 18,000 sq km covering Dar es Salaam and Coast regions.&nbsp;Rt. Rev. Jackson Sosthenes Jackson is the current Diocesan Bidhop who was concecrated and installed in February 2018. The Diocese is centred on the most westernized part of Tanzania, the city of Dar es Salaam. Although not officially the capital, that attribute is held by Dodoma, Dar es Salaam is very much the cultural and business capital of the country. St Albans’ Church became the Cathedral of the diocese on 11th July 2004.</p>', '', 1, 85, '2019-07-24 06:06:15', 42, 'Fruit Shop Webmaster', '2019-08-03 10:56:54', 42, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2019-07-24 06:06:15', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"article_layout":"","show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","info_block_show_title":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_associations":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_page_title":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 5, 3, '', '', 1, 0, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, '*', '', ''),
(21, 119, 'Bishop Maimbo W.F. Mndolwa .  Enthroned as Archbishop of the Anglican Church Of Tanzania.', 'bishop-maimbo-w-f-mndolwa-enthroned-as-archbishop-of-the-anglican-church-of-tanzania', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Today, May, 20,2018 in the day of Pentecost, the Anglican Church of Tanzania has enthroned Bishop Maimbo William Fabian Mndolwa, the bishop of the Diocese of Tanga, as the seventh Primate and Archbishop of the Anglican Church of Tanzania. Bishop Mndolwa has been officially enthroned in the service held at the Cathedral of the Holy Spirit in city of Dodoma.</p>\r\n', '\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The enthronement service which was officiated by Archbishop Dr. Jacob Erasto Chimeledya, was attended by various religious leaders and government officials, including the Prime Minister of the United Republic of Tanzania, Honorable Majaliwa Kassim Majaliwa, who represented the guest of honour, President of the United Republic of Tanzania, Honourable Dr. John Pombe Joseph Magufuli.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The service was attended by various international guests, including the bishop of Rochester, UK, Right Reverend James Langstaff, who represented the Archbishop of Canterbury, The Most Revd and Rt Hon Justin Welby.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Many visitors were impressed by the symbols of peace in Tanzania by witnessing the presence of senior government officials from nonChristian denominations using the Bible to convey a message of peace to the community. In his sermon, Archbishop Mndolwa promised to promote peace in the country in cooperation with the government. He said, when he spoke to the President, he registered his intention to call on the State House and meet with the President of Zanzibar to promote peace and prosperity. Archbishop Mndolwa also insisted that he will meet with other Christian and nonChristian leaders for the sake of maintaining national peace.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">As the Prime Minister delivered his speech, he emphasized that the Anglican Church of Tanzania has been in the forefront of promoting peace and that he will continue to cooperate with the church in all aspects of significant importance for the nation. He personally expressed his gratitude to the former Archbishop, The Most Rev Dr. Jacob Chimeledya for his outstanding achievements. Also, the Prime Minister praised the work done by the former Archbishop’s predecessors.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">He advised the newly enthroned Archbishop that he should not fear as the shoes worn by his predecessors, completely fit him. The Prime Minister said he will closely corporate with the newly enthroned Archbishop and assured him that he will identify him with favorite form of naming: Maimbo William Fabian Mndolwa. Under the Constitution of the Anglican Church of Tanzania, Bishop Mndolwa will serve as Archbishop for a period of five years.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The church invites all Christians to pray for the Primate and Archbishop Mndolwa in his service. Archbishop Mndolwa was born in Korogwe-Tanga, Tanzania, on 24/11/1969. His parents are Mndolwa Fabian Maimbo and Kauye-Agnes Mbelwa. Archbishop Mndolwa is the bishop of the Anglican Diocese of Tanga.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">He was consecrated into the order of a bishop on 04/9/2012. Archbishop Mndolwa is a Church historian, he has a PhD degree in theology, Church and Politics. Archbishop Mndolwa is married. His wife is Chenga Frida whom together they have been blessed with four children: Msagati-Katindi, Prisna-Kauye, Tahona and Challenge.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><em><strong>By God''s grace this statement has been issued to the public by: </strong></em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><em><strong>Rev Can Dr Mecka Ogunde The Secretary General, </strong></em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><em><strong>The Anglican Church of Tanzania </strong></em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><em><strong>20 May, 2018</strong></em></p>', 1, 89, '2019-07-24 06:06:15', 42, 'Joomla!', '2019-08-05 06:33:16', 42, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2019-07-24 06:06:15', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"article_layout":"","show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","info_block_show_title":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_associations":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_page_title":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 13, 11, '', '', 1, 16, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, '*', '', ''),
(22, 120, 'The Election of the Seventh Primate of the Anglican Church of Tanzania.', 'the-election-of-the-seventh-primate-of-the-anglican-church-of-tanzania', '<p style="text-align: justify;">The Special synod of the Anglican church of Tanzania which has met in accordance to the constitution of the Anglican Church of Tanzania, today on 15th February 2018 has elected the Rt Rev Maimbo Mndolwa the seventh Archbishop of the Anglican Church of Tanzania succeeding the incumbent Primate, Most Rev Dr Jacob Erasto Chimeledya who is looking forward in finishing his term in office in May this year.</p>\r\n', '\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Bishop Mndolwais the bishop of the Anglican diocese of Tanga. He was consecrated in the service of God in the holy order of a bishop on the Fourth day of the Nineth month of the year of our Lord of Two Thousand and Twelve. The Archbishop-elect told the synod, members of the Anglican Church of Tanzania, Anglicans worldwide and the general public that he has accepted the result of this election in humbleness and humility. He promised to work wholeheartedly for the benefit of the community and the Church as a whole. On his final blessings after the election, the Archbishop- elect insisted on peace, unity and listening to the voice of God in our lives. The Rt Rev Mndolwaas the Archbishop- elect will be installed as the Archbishop and Primate of the Anglican Church of Tanzania on 20th May 2018, the Day of Pentecoste.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Released by us by the Grace of God</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Rev. Can. Dr.Mecka Ogunde</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">GENERAL SECRETARY THE ANGLICAN CHURCH OF TANZANIA</p>', 1, 89, '2019-07-24 06:06:15', 42, '', '2019-08-05 06:28:21', 42, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2019-07-24 06:06:15', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_